&lt;p&gt;The Product Lead, Marketing &amp;amp; Adoption is responsible for driving awareness, understanding, and usage of RADaR’s product suite across the MTP agency network. This role serves as the bridge between the product team and the agencies and clients who use our tools, ensuring that every product launch lands with the right materials, messaging, and enablement to drive real adoption.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role combines product marketing execution, agency communication, and adoption management, with a primary focus on MTP intelligence strategy and adoption. The Product Lead, Marketing &amp;amp; Adoption translates complex analytics products into clear, compelling narratives and equips agency teams with the training, documentation, and support they need to get value from RADaR’s tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position does not have direct reports but requires strong cross-functional coordination with Product, Engineering, Agency Solutions, and Client teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ignore-global-css&quot;&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ignore-global-css&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ignore-global-css&quot;&gt;(Other duties may be assigned)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MTP Intelligence Strategy &amp;amp; Adoption&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the adoption strategy and execution for RADaR’s product suite across the MTP agency network, including CPA (Campaign Performance Assistant), MMM (Media Mix Modeling), CBI (Competitive Brand Intelligence), and emerging Business Intelligence and commerce solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain the positioning and messaging frameworks that translate technical product capabilities into agency-relevant value propositions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and execute go-to-market plans for product launches, version releases, and feature updates — coordinating timelines, deliverables, and cross-functional dependencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report on adoption metrics including active users, feature usage, product migration (e.g., Tableau-to-CPA), and agency engagement across the network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with agency leadership to align product adoption priorities with business objectives and client needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agency Enablement &amp;amp; Training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver onboarding materials, user guides, quick-start documentation, and training content for each product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and run agency webinars, product demos, and training sessions to drive awareness, confidence, and usage across the MTP network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage chat capability guides, prompt libraries, and “what can I ask?” documentation for AI-powered products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Top 30 client engagement push by partnering with the analytics team on data discovery conversations and product-readiness assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion change management for new product rollouts, ensuring agencies have what they need to adopt and sustain usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
